1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:422:"In May 2014, Dre Armeda announced that he was stepping down as CEO of Sucuri, Inc., a business that he started 4 years ago and turned into a very successful multi-million dollar, 30+ employee company that services millions of unique monthly scans, monitors &#8230; <a class="more-link" href="http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Lisa Sabin-Wilson";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3882:"<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-8405" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dre-armeda-300x300.jpg" alt="Dre Armeda Joins WebDevStudios" width="300" height="300" />In May 2014, Dre Armeda <a href="http://dremeda.com/fair-winds-and-following-seas-sucuri/">announced</a> that he was stepping down as CEO of Sucuri, Inc., a business that he started 4 years ago and turned into a very successful multi-million dollar, 30+ employee company that services millions of unique monthly scans, monitors thousands of websites, and makes sure that 100′s of websites are cleared of malware daily.  As a CISSP, Dre is a recognized expert in the field of Information Security.</p>\n<p>We are very proud, and excited, to announce that Dre has joined our leadership team here at WebDevStudios and has stepped into the role of VP of Operations with a focus on organizational and business development, talent development and strategy.</p>\n<p>Prior to running Sucuri, Dre was the founder of <em>Cubic 2</em>, a custom web design &amp; development shop that provided custom solutions for WordPress clients.  If that sounds familiar, that&#8217;s because that&#8217;s what we do here at WebDevStudios.  We are excited about bringing Dre&#8217;s experience and expertise into our team here at WDS, as we know his years of experience in information security &amp; architecture, managing remote teams, and his achievements in building and scaling a successful business will bring great value to our clients, and team, here at WebDevStudios.</p>\n<p>Dre&#8217;s excitement for open source software matches our own, and his passion for the WordPress project, in particular, is evident in his contributions to the community.  As a popular, and regular, <a href="http://wordpress.tv/speakers/dre-armeda/">speaker at WordCamps</a>, and related events, he is responsible for making an entire community of users and developers more aware of the importance of securing code and web sites by presenting it in a way that is easy to understand, while at the same time instilling a sense of urgency around making sure we all are doing what we can to secure our data and sites from the various risks out there in the WWW.</p>\n<p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-8406" src="http://webdevstudios.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/dradcast.png" alt="DradCast" width="200" height="223" />Dre also contributes to this community by way of a very popular, and informational, podcast that he co-hosts with our own Brad Williams.  <a href="http://dradcast.com">DradCast</a> airs every Wednesday evening at 8pm ET and is a show that primarily concentrates on the latest news around WordPress, upcoming WordPress events, and the wonderful community surrounding the premiere open source content management system on the internet.</p>\n<p>On a personal level, Dre resides in southern California and is a Harley enthusiast, a Chargers fan and he loves tacos. Having spent several years in the Navy, he shares the esteemed title of &#8220;former military geek&#8221; with Brad and Brian (both former Marines).</p>\n<p>We are thrilled to have Dre join our executive team here at WebDevStudios.  As we continue to grow and mature as a company, he plays a significant role in helping lead us into the future.  Our executive team is now complete with <a title="Brad Williams" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brad-williams/">Brad Williams</a>(CEO), <a title="Lisa Sabin-Wilson" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/lisa-sabin-wilson/">Lisa Sabin-Wilson</a> (COO), <a title="Brian Messenlehner" href="http://webdevstudios.com/team/brian-messenlehner/">Brian Messenlehner</a> (CTO) and now the addition of Dre Armeda as VP of Operations, we are excited for the future of our team and for our clients!</p>\n<p>Please join us in welcoming Dre as the newest member to the WDS team!</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/14/dre-armeda-joins-webdevstudios/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"9";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"Which Brad Will You Be Seeing at WordCamp Grand Rapids 2014?";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:96:"http://webdevstudios.com/2014/08/12/which-brad-will-you-be-seeing-at-wordcamp-grand-rapids-2014/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:105:"http://