(2713, 215, 'additional_info', 'Gene Pizzolato is president and general manager of Gamut. In this role, Pizzolato oversees Gamut’s four business units, which collectively offer a broad spectrum media solutions for advertisers and publishers. Pizzolato assumed his current position from his role as president and general manager of Cox Digital Solutions and Cox Cross Media. Pizzolato joined Cox in 2013. \r\n\r\nPizzolato brings a full spectrum of expertise to Gamut, including: operations, marketing promotion, client direct partner engagement, digital business, cable and sports. Prior to joining Cox, Pizzolato was under special assignment for Gannett Broadcasting, a leading media and marketing solutions company that delivers content and services across an integrated, multi-platform portfolio. There, he spearheaded the record-setting sales and marketing efforts for the London Olympics and built the Sochi Olympics strategic roadmap, which was recently executed across all Gannett NBC stations.\r\n\r\nPizzolato began his career in broadcasting. He was a member of the initial leadership team at the Golf Channel, where he held positions of chief operating officer, chief revenue officer and chief marketing officer. During his tenure, he launched the network, where valuations rose from $1 billion to $2.4 billion.\r\n\r\nPizzolato is a graduate from State University of New York College at Oswego, where he received a degree in communications studies. '),
(2714, 215, '_additional_info', 'field_5419deabd7bca'),
